&lt;p&gt;Do you have an interest in working in End Of Life Care?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Would you like to work in a supportive multidisciplinary team?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Do you want the opportunity to develop specialist practice skills?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Then this is the perfect role for you-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salisbury Hospice are seeking to appoint enthusiastic and highly motivated band 5 registered Nurses to join our team. Preferably with experience for caring for people with life limiting conditions to work in our inpatient unit. You will be able to demonstrate highest standards of nursing care alongside excellent communication and interpersonal skills, the ability to work well within a team and with other multi-professional colleagues, and the desire to provide high quality nursing care are all essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to providing staff with learning and development opportunities to support their career progression. We also offer on-site subsidised childcare, flexible working and a generous pension. We have both Full time and Part time positions available and the team work on an internal rotation which you will be expected to take part in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salisbury NHS hold four core values that guide our day-to-day work with patients, colleagues and stakeholders. These are: patient centred and safe, professional, responsive, and friendly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mandy Coombes Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;mandy.coombes1@nhs.net 01722 425113 / 01722 336262 ext 2365&lt;/p&gt;
